comments: Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Speldhurst.

Created 1894 out of the parishes of Tonbridge and Leigh. See also 
    Table 2, notes (c) and (k).

On 30.9.1895 the part in East Sussex was transferred to Kent, so that thereafter Horsmondon was wholly in Kent. See also 
    Table 2, note (k).

Created 1.4.1969 out of the London borough of Bromley. See also 
    Table 2, notes (i) and (k).

Created 1.4.1955 out of the parish of Brenchley. See also Table 
    2, note (k).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Tonbridge in Southborough 
    Urban District. See also Table 2, note (k).

Abolished 1894 and divided between the parishes of Tunbridge Wells, 
    Tonbridge Urban, Southborough, Tonbridge Rural and Hildenborough.

Created 1.4.1934 out of the parishes of Tonbridge Urban, Hadlow, 
    Tonbridge Rural and Hildenborough. Abolished 1.4.1974 to become the 
    Tonbridge & Malling unparished 
    area.

Unparished area which until 1.4.1974 formed the parish  of Tonbridge. See also Table 2, note 
    (k).

Created 1894 out of the parishes of Tonbridge and Frant. Abolished 
    1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Pembury, Tunbridge Wells, Capel, 
    Tonbridge and Southborough. See also Table 2, note (a).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Tonbridge in Tonbridge 
    Urban District. Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Tonbridge.
Abolished 25.3.1885 and added to the parish of Capel.

Created 1894 from the pars of the parishes of Tonbridge and Speldhurst 
    in Tunbridge Wells Municipal Borough. Abolished 1.4.1974 to become an unparished 
    area. See also Table 2, note (f).

Unparished area which until 1.4.1974 formed the parish of Tunbridge Wells. See also Table 
    2, note (k).
